Scanner class 
------------

Scanner class is used to read input from the keyboard.

Scanner class has two constructors.


Creating Scanner class object

Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);//system.in is the default input stream (represents the keyboard).


Scanner class methods
---------------------
1.nextInt()
2.nextDouble()
3.nextFloat()
4.nextLong()
5.nextShort()
6.nextByte()
7.nextBoolean()
8.next()
9.hasNext()
10.nextLine()
11.hasNextLine()
12.nextBigInteger()
13.nextBigDecimal()
14.nextBigInteger()
15.nextBigDecimal()

nextInt()
---------
Reads an integer from the input stream.

nextDouble()
------------
Reads a double from the input stream.

nextFloat()
-----------
Reads a float from the input stream.

nextLong()
----------
Reads a long from the input stream.

nextShort()
-----------
Reads a short from the input stream.

nextByte()
----------
Reads a byte from the input stream.

nextBoolean()
-------------
Reads a boolean from the input stream.

next()
------
Reads a string from the input stream.

hasNext()
---------
Checks if there is another token available on the input stream.

nextLine()
----------
Reads the next line from the input stream.

hasNextLine()
-------------
Checks if there is another line available on the input stream.

nextBigInteger()
----------------
Reads a BigInteger from the input stream.

nextBigDecimal()
------------------    
Reads a BigDecimal from the input stream.

